		<q:key answer="MIDIa_3"/>
	</q:item>
</exercise><para id="id1170543511484">In both cases, you probably found it easy to pick out the “wrong” note.</para>
    <para id="id1170545225658"><term>Dissonance</term> creates harmonic <emphasis>opacity</emphasis>. It makes chord identification more difficult: It is harder to distinguish the constituent sounds. </para>
    <para id="id1170519680849">Here is a <term>dissonant</term> chord from Olivier Messiaen’s <emphasis>Vision de l’Amen.</emphasis></para>
    <example id="eip-620"><media id="id11700366549316" alt="" display="block"><audio src="Messiaen01" id="Messiaen01" mime-type="audio/mpeg"><param name="composer" value="Olivier Messiaen"/><param name="title" value="Visions de l'Amen"/><param name="comments" value="Sarah Rothenberg and Marilyn Nonken, pianos"/><param name="total-time" value="10"/><param name="label-number" value="Bridge Records"/><param name="performer" value=""/></audio></media>
</example><para id="id1170529070176">Which of these pitches doesn’t belong?:</para>
    <exercise id="eip-164"><q:item id="item_mida1" type="single-response">
		<q:question>
			<section id="s_mida1">
				<para id="p_mida1"> 
<media id="id1594805a1" alt="" display="block"><audio src="MIDI24" id="MIDI24" mime-type="audio/mpeg"><param name="composer" value=""/><param name="title" value="Pitch I"/><param name="comments" value=""/><param name="total-time" value=""/><param name="label-number" value=""/><param name="performer" value=""/></audio></media>
 
<media id="id1594806a1" alt="" display="block"><audio src="MIDI25" id="MIDI25" mime-type="audio/mpeg"><param name="composer" value=""/><param name="title" value="Pitch II"/><param name="comments" value=""/><param name="total-time" value=""/><param name="label-number" value=""/><param name="performer" value=""/></audio></media>

